880
00:46:42,880 --> 00:46:45,639
So maybe you'll finish
before midnight!

881
00:46:45,640 --> 00:46:48,519
Could I speak to Mrs Gordon,
please?

882
00:46:48,520 --> 00:46:49,679
You've got the wrong number.

883
00:46:49,680 --> 00:46:51,559
No, I mean, sorry, I mean

884
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:52,399
Mrs Roberts.

885
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:54,959
Mrs Ethel Roberts.

886
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:57,039
That was my mother's name
before she was married.

887
00:46:57,040 --> 00:46:58,159
Who is this?

888
00:46:58,160 --> 00:46:58,879
My name is Jimmy.

889
00:46:58,880 --> 00:47:00,479
Could I speak to her?

890
00:47:00,480 --> 00:47:02,119
About what?

891
00:47:02,120 --> 00:47:08,359
I'm calling from Belfast and
I don't have a lot of money.

892
00:47:08,360 --> 00:47:11,159
All right, just a minute.

893
00:47:11,160 --> 00:47:15,000
Pennsylvania 6-5000

894
00:47:15,640 --> 00:47:16,320
Mom?

895
00:47:16,560 --> 00:47:17,480
Yes.

896
00:47:17,760 --> 00:47:21,320
There's a phone call for you.

897
00:47:22,360 --> 00:47:24,679
Will you pick up the phone?

898
00:47:24,680 --> 00:47:27,119
No, thanks, sweetheart.

899
00:47:27,120 --> 00:47:27,880
Mom?

900
00:47:28,320 --> 00:47:30,279
No, thank you.

901
00:47:30,280 --> 00:47:35,080
It's a man, says he's from Belfast.

902
00:47:37,840 --> 00:47:39,560
Mom?

903
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:51,719
Pennsylvania 6-5000

904
00:47:51,720 --> 00:47:55,599
She doesn't wanna answer,
you'll have to leave a message.

905
00:47:55,600 --> 00:47:56,360
Hello?

906
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:57,880
Hello?

907
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,839
Can you hear me?

908
00:47:59,840 --> 00:48:03,159
Now, just a minute, please.

909
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:04,040
Mom?

910
00:48:04,280 --> 00:48:04,800
Hello?

911
00:48:05,200 --> 00:48:06,959
Did you pick up?

912
00:48:06,960 --> 00:48:08,280
Hello?

913
00:48:09,240 --> 00:48:10,800
Hello?

914
00:48:11,640 --> 00:48:13,440
Hello?

915
00:48:13,680 --> 00:48:14,240
Hello?

916
00:48:14,480 --> 00:48:16,039
Who is this, please?

917
00:48:16,040 --> 00:48:17,839
My name is Jimmy Reilly.

918
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:21,119
I'm calling from Belfast.

919
00:48:21,120 --> 00:48:23,599
Could I speak to Ethel.

920
00:48:23,600 --> 00:48:25,999
I'm sorry, I'm not sure
what her name is now.

921
00:48:26,000 --> 00:48:27,400
Marie?

922
00:48:27,920 --> 00:48:31,119
Marie, you can hang up now,
please.

923
00:48:31,120 --> 00:48:32,520
Okay.

924
00:48:35,760 --> 00:48:38,159
They told me she
wouldn't have the same address,

925
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:42,719
not after 50 years
but I thought I'd try anyway.

926
00:48:42,720 --> 00:48:45,639
Are you there?

927
00:48:45,640 --> 00:48:47,039
What do you want?

928
00:48:47,040 --> 00:48:49,119
I have something
belonging to you.

929
00:48:49,120 --> 00:48:51,359
Well, I think it belongs to you.

930
00:48:51,360 --> 00:48:52,559
It's a ring.

931
00:48:52,560 --> 00:48:53,279
A gold ring.

932
00:48:53,280 --> 00:48:55,319
It's got names on the inside.

933
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:56,000
A ring?

934
00:48:56,240 --> 00:48:56,880
Yeah

935
00:48:57,120 --> 00:49:00,559
It says 'Ethel and Teddy'.

936
00:49:00,560 --> 00:49:01,640
Hello?

937
00:49:01,840 --> 00:49:04,479
Can you hear me?

938
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:05,279
Oh, bugger!

939
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:05,959
Wait a minute

940
00:49:05,960 --> 00:49:09,039
wait wait there.

941
00:49:09,040 --> 00:49:10,759
Please, do you have any money?

942
00:49:10,760 --> 00:49:12,799
I do, and I've a mind to use it

943
00:49:12,800 --> 00:49:15,079
if you would get
the frig out of there!

944
00:49:15,080 --> 00:49:15,560
Oh God.

945
00:49:15,840 --> 00:49:18,119
Look, listen to me,
I'll call you back.

946
00:49:18,120 --> 00:49:18,520
Okay?

947
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:19,880
Hello?

948
00:49:20,480 --> 00:49:24,560
I'll call you back.

949
00:49:26,720 --> 00:49:28,160
Bugger.

950
00:49:31,280 --> 00:49:32,759
Sorry, America.

951
00:49:32,760 --> 00:49:33,479
Long distance.

952
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,199
You could have walked there
in that time!

953
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:38,560
I wish he would.

954
00:49:48,720 --> 00:49:50,599
Mr Quinlan?

955
00:49:50,600 --> 00:49:51,080
It's me.

956
00:49:51,360 --> 00:49:54,680
Mr Quinlan?

957
00:49:58,080 --> 00:49:59,079
Bloody hell!

958
00:49:59,080 --> 00:50:00,879
It's 6.30 in the morning!

959
00:50:00,880 --> 00:50:01,799
Please, I need a phone.

960
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:03,039
It's really urgent.

961
00:50:03,040 --> 00:50:04,119
I found something.

962
00:50:04,120 --> 00:50:05,639
Well, it wasn't your brains,
was it?

963
00:50:05,640 --> 00:50:06,279
Go to hell!

964
00:50:06,280 --> 00:50:07,119
I found a ring!

965
00:50:07,120 --> 00:50:08,279
On the mountain.

966
00:50:08,280 --> 00:50:09,199
A gold ring.

967
00:50:09,200 --> 00:50:11,919
It belonged to one of the crew.

968
00:50:11,920 --> 00:50:13,279
It's got names on it.

969
00:50:13,280 --> 00:50:14,919
I went to the library
and they told me

970
00:50:14,920 --> 00:50:16,639
to call
the Veterans Administration

971
00:50:16,640 --> 00:50:18,959
only I had to keep calling,
and it cost a packet.

972
00:50:18,960 --> 00:50:21,119
And when my granny found out,
she went apeshit.

973
00:50:21,120 --> 00:50:23,319
So, I had to use the phone box
and call America,

974
00:50:23,320 --> 00:50:25,239
but I ran out of money,
and that was last night,

975
00:50:25,240 --> 00:50:26,599
and I have to call her back!

976
00:50:26,600 --> 00:50:27,120
Who?

977
00:50:27,360 --> 00:50:28,600
Ethel.

978
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:30,799
The name on the ring

979
00:50:30,800 --> 00:50:31,519
You wanna see it?

980
00:50:31,520 --> 00:50:32,319
No, I don't.

981
00:50:32,320 --> 00:50:33,919
I don't want it.

982
00:50:33,920 --> 00:50:34,560
Get out.

983
00:50:34,800 --> 00:50:35,360
Get out!

984
00:50:35,600 --> 00:50:37,439
Mr Quinlan.

985
00:50:37,440 --> 00:50:38,399
Are you all right?

986
00:50:38,400 --> 00:50:39,479
So, you found it.

987
00:50:39,480 --> 00:50:40,999
You stupid bugger!

988
00:50:41,000 --> 00:50:43,839
Doesn't mean a damn thing to you,
but you found it!

989
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:45,119
And then what do you do?

990
00:50:45,120 --> 00:50:47,999
After 50 years, you just call her
up out of the blue!

991
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:49,719
"Oh, guess what I've got!"

992
00:50:49,720 --> 00:50:52,519
Well, I thought she'd be pleased.

993
00:50:52,520 --> 00:50:55,279
Only, I was halfway through,
and I ran out of money.

994
00:50:55,280 --> 00:50:58,719
What do you want me
to do about that?

995
00:50:58,720 --> 00:51:02,920
Well, I just wanted to
use your phone.

996
00:51:04,200 --> 00:51:05,480
Get inside

997
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:07,040
Come on.

998
00:51:13,320 --> 00:51:14,599
I don't believe it!

999
00:51:14,600 --> 00:51:16,359
This is incredible.

1000
00:51:16,360 --> 00:51:17,319
All this stuff.

1001
00:51:17,320 --> 00:51:18,439
Don't touch it.

1002
00:51:18,440 --> 00:51:19,919
This is fantastic!

1003
00:51:19,920 --> 00:51:20,879
Phone is there.

1004
00:51:20,880 --> 00:51:22,120
Go on.

1005
00:51:22,360 --> 00:51:25,680
And be quick.

1006
00:51:39,440 --> 00:51:43,040
Three six nine two?

1007
00:51:43,040 --> 00:51:45,319
Yes, who is it?

1008
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:46,040
Gander?

1009
00:51:47,760 --> 00:51:49,439
Do you know anyone in Gander?

1010
00:51:49,440 --> 00:51:50,999
Yeah, it's an airbase.

1011
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:51,400
Teddy!

1012
00:51:51,640 --> 00:51:52,759
Yes, I'll pay!

1013
00:51:52,760 --> 00:51:53,760
Teddy?

1014
00:51:54,000 --> 00:51:54,759
See you Jack.

1015
00:51:54,760 --> 00:51:57,119
Ethel Ann?
No, it's not Teddy, it's Jack.

1016
00:51:57,120 --> 00:51:58,040
Sorry.

1017
00:51:58,240 --> 00:51:59,120
Jack, hi!

1018
00:51:59,360 --> 00:52:00,559
How are you?

1019
00:52:00,560 --> 00:52:01,919
Oh, it's so good to
hear from you.

1020
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:05,199
Where the heck is Gander?

1021
00:52:05,200 --> 00:52:06,599
Newfoundland.

1022
00:52:06,600 --> 00:52:08,079
Well, what's it like up there?

1023
00:52:08,080 --> 00:52:09,080
Raining.

1024
00:52:10,320 --> 00:52:12,599
Are you on your own?

1025
00:52:12,600 --> 00:52:17,159
No, Chuck got back a week ago.

1026
00:52:17,160 --> 00:52:20,959
He hurt himself,
but he's okay now.

1027
00:52:20,960 --> 00:52:23,319
Hey, you should see me
in my nurse's uniform.

1028
00:52:23,320 --> 00:52:25,359
I'm training to be a nurse.

1029
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:27,199
Chuck says I look great.

1030
00:52:27,200 --> 00:52:28,919
I bet you do.

1031
00:52:28,920 --> 00:52:30,799
It's so good to hear from you.

1032
00:52:30,800 --> 00:52:32,519
Have you spoken to Teddy?

1033
00:52:32,520 --> 00:52:34,559
Is he okay?

1034
00:52:34,560 --> 00:52:40,199
The last I saw him, he was good,
but I broke my ankle.

1035
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:40,800
Yeah.

1036
00:52:41,040 --> 00:52:42,479
I was dancing.

1037
00:52:42,480 --> 00:52:44,679
So, I'm coming home on leave.

1038
00:52:44,680 --> 00:52:46,279
Jack, you're crazy!

1039
00:52:46,280 --> 00:52:50,079
He broke his ankle in a dance.

1040
00:52:50,080 --> 00:52:53,279
Hey, can I talk to Chuck?

1041
00:52:53,280 --> 00:52:54,000
Yeah.

1042
00:52:55,080 --> 00:52:55,879
He wants to talk to you.

1043
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:58,559
But then I wanna talk to
you again, okay?

1044
00:52:58,560 --> 00:52:59,320
Here.

1045
00:52:59,560 --> 00:53:00,360
Thanks.

